	<div class="tm-article-content uk-position-relative  tm-article-date-true">

				<div class="tm-article-date uk-text-center">
		    <span class="tm-article-date-day">18</span><span class="tm-article-date-month">Jul</span>		</div>
		


		<h1 class="uk-article-title">
					7 Tips to learn Chinese			</h1>
	
	

		<p class="uk-article-meta">

		
	</p>
	

	
		<div>
		
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;">Learning Chinese is a hard work, but we give you some tips to make your learning journey easier.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;"></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;">1. Understand that Mandarin while difficult can also be easy to learn.</span></strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;">Chinese is considered as one of the most difficult languages, and in some sense, this is true; especially if we are talking about pronouncing properly tones and memorizing characters.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;">However, we always have to look at the bright side. What most non-Chinese do not know is that Mandarin has one of the easiest grammars in the World. The structure of the sentences is always the same (subject + verb + object), there is no gender, no plural nouns, and verbs don&rsquo;t have conjugations.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;"></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span>2. Do not just say &lsquo;no&rsquo; to characters</span></strong></span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;">Characters are the main part of Mandarin as well as the alphabet is for others. Moreover, in the long-term, memorizing characters will be way easier than just memorizing pinying. I do recommend you to learn simplified Chinese than the traditional one since it is way easier to memorize:</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><img src="http://blog.betterchinese.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/traditional-simplified.jpg" alt="" width="371" height="236" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" /></span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;">Plus, if you do not learn character, you lost the chance to learn from street signs, newspapers, magazines, etc. But if you only want to learn Mandarin for mere oral communication, fell free to ignore the characters.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;"></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;">3. Don&rsquo;t always trust your books.</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;">In all the textbooks, you will be taught how to say these sentences:</span></p>
<p style="margin: 3.5pt 0cm 0.5pt 30px; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><em><span>&nbsp; </span></em><em><span>Nǐ hǎo ma</span></em></span></p>
<p style="margin: 3.5pt 0cm 0.5pt 30px; text-indent: 18pt; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span>"</span><em><span>你好吗</span></em><span>?&rdquo;&nbsp; </span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span>-&gt;</span><span> &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span> "<em>How are you</em>"</span></span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: 36pt; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><em><span>Hěn gāox&igrave;ng r&egrave;nsh&igrave; nǐ&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></em><span class="apple-converted-space"><em></em></span></span></p>
<p style="margin: 3.75pt 0cm 0.5pt 30px; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span class="apple-converted-space"><em><span>&ldquo;</span></em></span><em><span>很高兴认识你</span></em><span>" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp; -&gt;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span>"<em>Nice to meet you</em>". &nbsp;</span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 15pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span>However, w</span><span>e don't really use<em>&nbsp;</em></span><em><span>these two sentences</span></em><span>&nbsp;as often as you would say&nbsp;<em>How are you</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Nice to meet you</em>&nbsp;in English.</span></span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 15pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;">For &ldquo;<em>How are you&rdquo;</em>, one of the better options you can say instead is:</span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: 36pt; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><em><span>Zu&igrave;j&igrave;n nǐ zěnmey&agrave;ng</span></em><em></em></span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: 36pt; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><em><span>最近你怎么样</span></em><span>&nbsp;?&nbsp;<em>(How's everything lately?&nbsp;</em></span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><em style="line-height: 18pt; text-indent: 36pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span>4. Don&rsquo;t get nervous when Chinese people do not understand you</span></strong></em></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;">Chinese people are not good at understanding foreign accent since it is kind of a new thing that foreigners are learning Mandarin. Plus, they do not usually show effort on trying to understand you because they take for granted that you are not speaking Chinese. So be confident and just repeat yourself if they don&rsquo;t understand you the first time. To learn a language is all about practicing it, especially Mandarin, which has nothing to do with European languages</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;"></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span>5. Don&rsquo;t expect everyone to sound the same</span></strong></span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;">As any other country, we have different accents in China depending on where are we from since we also have over 400 dialects. I know it seems unfair that we understand each other but cannot understand foreign accent, but the trick part is the tone. It is very important since different tones might have different meanings:</span></p>
<p><img src="http://www.taiwanese-secrets.com/image-files/facts-about-mandarin-chinese2.003.jpg" alt="" width="427" height="180" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong style="line-height: 18pt; text-align: center; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><span>6. Listen to Chinese songs and follow Chinese TV Shows/Series</span></strong></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;">This is one of the best ways to learn Chinese since you can listen and read at the same time. Therefore, you can practice pronunciation and learn new characters and its meanings within a context.</span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;">Here you can find a list of the 10 most popular TV Shows in China:</span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><a href="http://www.chinawhisper.com/top-10-chinese-tv-shows/"><span>http://www.chinawhisper.com/top-10-chinese-tv-shows/</span></a></span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;">Here you can find a list of 10 popular Chinese TV dramas:</span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span><a href="http://www.china.org.cn/top10/2014-04/07/content_32005194.htm">http://www.china.org.cn/top10/2014-04/07/content_32005194.htm</a><a href="http://www.china.org.cn/top10/2014-04/07/content_32005194.htm"></a></span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Calibri;">As to practice your Chinese and voice, you can always go to a KTV (Chinese Karaoke), where you can have a great time while improving your Mandarin level.</span></p>
<p><img src="https://ehevphotography.files.wordpress.com/2011/05/img_0048.jpg" alt="" width="336" height="224" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" /><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;"></span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;">7. Take it seriously</span></strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;">It is much recommended to start learning Mandarin in an established Chinese course since you are not going to learn Chinese in a week (unless you have unusual aptitude for learning foreign languages). After learning the basics, you can look for a person who is native Chinese speaker in order to improve your level.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 115%;">Unlike Western languages, Mandarin is a non-alphabetic language and it might make you very tired to keep going. But as any other language, what you need to do is to keep practicing it and don&rsquo;t give up. After a while, you are going to see your improvements and being able to communicate with a native Chinese will give you much satisfaction!</span></p> 	</div>
	
	
	
	


	</div>




</article>
